Late President 's Legacy Still Valuable for China : Officials ( 1 )
BEIJING , November 19 ( Xinhua ) - Late Chinese President Liu Shaoqi 's theories on building the Chinese Communist Party ( CPC ) and his thoughts on economics and the construction of a democratic legal system are still of guiding significance for today 's China , top officials said here today .
Wei Jianxing , a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee , and two former officials , Gu Mu and Wang Hanbin , made these comments here today .
They were speaking at the opening ceremony of a five-day symposium on the life and thought of the late Chinese president .
Hu Jintao , State vice president , also attended the meeting today .
Liu was acclaimed for having " performed acts of undeniable merit in the cause of the Chinese revolution and construction . "
He was the first chairman of the National People 's Congress Standing Committee and later served as President of the State .
But he died as a result of political persecution on November 12 , 1969 .
Wei said that Liu expounded the position and role of Mao Zedong and his thoughts in the Chinese Communist Revolution , and made historic contributions to the establishment of Mao Zedong Thoughts as guiding principles of the Party .
